   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON TWELVE THE GRACE-MINISTERING SERVICE Scripture Reading: Rom 12:4-6a, 7a; Eph 4:7; 1 Pet 4:10; John 1:17b; 1 Cor 15:10; 2 Cor 12:9 OUTLINE All the members of the Body of Christ being gifted Rom 12:6a.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Every member having been given grace Eph 4:7; Rom 12:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>All the members being stewards of the varied grace of God 1 Pet 4:10.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The service in the church being the function of the members with grace.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Grace being God embodied in Christ as our enjoyment John 1:17b; 1 Cor 15:10.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To serve in the church being to minister Christ as grace to others: First, we need to experience the grace of Christ in our own circumstances 2 Cor 12:9.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Then we minister grace to others through our service.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The goal of our service: Not to accomplish things.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>But to infuse others with Christ as grace.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
